# lean-ctx — optional context compression

Alfred ships lean-ctx for token savings. It complements — does not replace — native Cursor tools or domain MCPs.

## Default
- **Read / Grep / Shell / Glob** → native Cursor tools
- **Edit / Write** → native Cursor tools

## When lean-ctx helps
| Situation | Tool |
|-----------|------|
| Skim a large file | `ctx_read(path, "map")` or `ctx_read(path, "lines:N-M")` |
| Search a big repo | `ctx_search(pattern, path)` |
| Noisy git/npm output | `lean-ctx -c "git log --oneline -20"` |
| Cross-session facts | `ctx_knowledge` remember / recall |

## Bail-out rule
If lean-ctx MCP errors or exceeds ~5 seconds, **do not retry** — use native tools for the rest of the turn.

Do not call `ctx_overview` or `ctx_compose` on every turn.
